Hi, my name is Nancy and I am one of the people that POV asked to help facilitate this discussion.  In the film, Lisa talks about her boyfriend Willie and how he was controlling of her time and her relationships with friends.  Eventually Lisa was able to see that this relationship made her unhappy so she got out of it.  From what people have posted so far it seems like a lot of us have been in relationshps where maybe we had strong feelings for the person, but we ultimately couldn't live with them trying to control us and our lives.<br><br>
I wonder why we get in these relationships to begin with?  What makes some girls so vulnerable to being controlled by their boyfriends?  People here have said that experiencing bad relationships as a teenager is part of a growing process where you learn what works for you and what doesn't. Is it mostly the case that people have to go through this painful process before they can find someone who makes them happy and treats them with respect?  For those of you who have gotten out of bad relationships, what was the turning point that made you realize that you needed to make a change?
